== archive-tar

Archive-Tar is a library to extract and create tar archives without external
tools.

=== Extracting an tar archive

    require "archive/tar.rb"
    file = File.new("foo.tar.gz")
    tar_reader = Archive::Tar::Reader.new(file)
    
    tar_reader.extract_all("foo/")

=== Creating a tar archive
    
    require "archive/tar.rb"
    file = File.new("foo.tar")
    tar_writer = Archive::Tar::Writer.new(file)
    
    tar_writer.add_file("foo")
    tar_writer.add_file("bar")
    # The second argument says, whether to use or not to use the full path
    # The third argument says, whether to read the directory recursive
    #   or non-recursive
    tar_writer.add_directory("baz/", false, true)
